y Sir Hugh Cortazzi, focuses on the post-war history up to the present day. Published in association with the Japan Society, its appearance marks the abdication of Emperor Akihito and the enthronement of Crown Prince Naruhito in May 2019. It is also a memorial volume to the late Sir Hugh Cortazzi who died in August 2018, shortly after completing his own contribution to the volume.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDiplomatic relations. 4aAsian Studies. 4aAsian history. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aHistory. 4aInternational Relations. 4aJapan. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh  aBritain.  aJapan.  adiplomacy.  aemperor.  afirst world war.  aking.  amonarchy.1 aBest, Anthony, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBest, Antony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBest, Antony.1 aCortazzi, Hugh, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCortazzi, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortazzi, Hugh.1 aKornicki, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKornicki, Peter.1 aTsuruoka, Koji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarren, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066152140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781898823872?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781898823872423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781898823872/original  a978-3-11-066152-1  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL 